 {"id":"asupersync-3kv3e.1","title":"[audit][stream] Latch Filter/FilterMap exhaustion to avoid repolling upstream after Ready(None)","description":"src/stream/filter.rs currently returns Poll::Ready(None) directly from Filter::poll_next and FilterMap::poll_next without latching terminal exhaustion. After completion, later polls re-enter the upstream stream and can repoll exhausted inner streams, unlike current repo style in enumerate/skip/zip and recent fail-closed audit fixes. Add per-combinator exhausted state, zero size_hint after exhaustion, focused regression tests proving exhausted upstreams are not repolled for both Filter and FilterMap, and validate with rch-offloaded fmt/check/clippy/test commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaDeer","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-12T21:22:05.614701956Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T21:53:21.663552413Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream","terminal-state"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-3kv3e.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3kv3e","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T21:22:05.614701956Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
